parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

symptoms: causing the windshield wipers to stop working or malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or shut down, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Timing chain failure can cause engine failure, leading to stalling or shutting down, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Rear main seal failure can cause engine oil leaks, leading to engine failure and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Excessive oil consumption can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to the catalytic converter and other engine components.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
often requiring frequent oil changes. The oil light may not come on
and the vehicle may not display any warning signs until the engine fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: The engine may stall or shut off
and the vehicle may experience rough idling or surging. The timing chain may break

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear main seal failure can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience oil leaks
and the engine may fail due to low oil pressure. The rear main seal may fail

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause loss of motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: The transmission may slip or hesitate
causing the vehicle to lose power. The vehicle may experience difficulty shifting gears or may become stuck in a particular gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: The engine may stall or shut off
often without warning. The vehicle may experience difficulty starting or may stall repeatedly.
